In this section, we present the results of our patient-tracking protocol as well as the two stages of our prospective study. As part of our tracking protocol, we show in the bottom panel of Fig. 2, the number of patients who start off at stage 1 in each wave (EW-2 through EW-5), as well as the number transitioning to each of stages 2, 3, and 4. Despite the severity of the pandemic, the number of patients transitioning to higher stages is relatively low. Fortunately, most patients do not suffer complications and remain at stage 1 until discharge. Since our patient-tracking protocol begins by identifying patients at stage 1 within the first \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
